$ C standards

C standards (as also → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/CPP/standards[C++ standards]) are usually named after the year in which they were published.

{ C89

  The → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC[gcc] → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options[option] → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options/std[`-std=c89`] or `-ansi`
  enforces this standard.

}
{ C99 #c99

  Apparently, C99 introduced among others
    • `bool` (`<stdbool.h>`)
    • `int32_t` etc. (`<stdint.h>`)
    • `for (int i = …) {}`
    • `snprintf` (see → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc#printf-family[printf family]).
    • → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/CPP[C++] like comments (`//`)

}
sa:
  GCC's → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options/std[`-std=…`] option.
